{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Let's imagine a sculptor\nbuilding a statue,"},{"time":3760,"text":"just chipping away with his chisel."},{"time":6160,"text":"Michelangelo had this elegant way\nof describing it when he said,"},{"time":9240,"text":"\"Every block of stone\nhas a statue inside of it,"},{"time":12160,"text":"and it's the task\nof the sculptor to discover it.\""},{"time":15280,"text":"But what if he worked\nin the opposite direction?"},{"time":17720,"text":"Not from a solid block of stone,"},{"time":19600,"text":"but from a pile of dust,"},{"time":21320,"text":"somehow gluing millions of these particles\ntogether to form a statue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25720,"text":"I know that's an absurd notion."},{"time":27240,"text":"It's probably impossible."},{"time":29000,"text":"The only way you get\na statue from a pile of dust"},{"time":31960,"text":"is if the statue built itself --"},{"time":34320,"text":"if somehow we could compel millions\nof these particles to come together"},{"time":38480,"text":"to form the statue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40320,"text":"Now, as odd as that sounds,"},{"time":41880,"text":"that is almost exactly the problem\nI work on in my lab."},{"time":46040,"text":"I don't build with stone,"},{"time":47480,"text":"I build with nanomaterials."},{"time":48880,"text":"They're these just impossibly small,\nfascinating little objects."},{"time":53280,"text":"They're so small that if this controller\nwas a nanoparticle,"},{"time":56600,"text":"a human hair would be the size\nof this entire room."},{"time":59560,"text":"And they're at the heart of a field\nwe call nanotechnology,"},{"time":62400,"text":"which I'm sure we've all heard about,"},{"time":64239,"text":"and we've all heard\nhow it is going to change everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67720,"text":"When I was a graduate student,"},{"time":69240,"text":"it was one of the most exciting times\nto be working in nanotechnology."},{"time":72600,"text":"There were scientific breakthroughs\nhappening all the time."},{"time":75840,"text":"The conferences were buzzing,"},{"time":77280,"text":"there was tons of money\npouring in from funding agencies."},{"time":80760,"text":"And the reason is"},{"time":82040,"text":"when objects get really small,"},{"time":83880,"text":"they're governed by a different set\nof physics that govern ordinary objects,"},{"time":87520,"text":"like the ones we interact with."},{"time":89040,"text":"We call this physics quantum mechanics."},{"time":91000,"text":"And what it tells you is\nthat you can precisely tune their behavior"},{"time":94200,"text":"just by making seemingly\nsmall changes to them,"},{"time":96520,"text":"like adding or removing\na handful of atoms,"},{"time":99160,"text":"or twisting the material."},{"time":100880,"text":"It's like this ultimate toolkit."},{"time":102680,"text":"You really felt empowered;\nyou felt like you could make anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105800,"text":"And we were doing it --"},{"time":107080,"text":"and by we I mean my whole\ngeneration of graduate students."},{"time":110200,"text":"We were trying to make blazing fast\ncomputers using nanomaterials."},{"time":113720,"text":"We were constructing quantum dots"},{"time":115360,"text":"that could one day go in your body\nand find and fight disease."},{"time":118760,"text":"There were even groups\ntrying to make an elevator to space"},{"time":121800,"text":"using carbon nanotubes."},{"time":123600,"text":"You can look that up, that's true."},{"time":126776,"text":"Anyways, we thought it was going to affect"},{"time":128800,"text":"all parts of science and technology,\nfrom computing to medicine."},{"time":131920,"text":"And I have to admit,"},{"time":133200,"text":"I drank all of the Kool-Aid."},{"time":135200,"text":"I mean, every last drop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138520,"text":"But that was 15 years ago,"},{"time":141160,"text":"and --"},{"time":142400,"text":"fantastic science was done,\nreally important work."},{"time":144800,"text":"We've learned a lot."},{"time":146080,"text":"We were never able to translate\nthat science into new technologies --"},{"time":150480,"text":"into technologies\nthat could actually impact people."},{"time":153280,"text":"And the reason is, these nanomaterials --"},{"time":155520,"text":"they're like a double-edged sword."},{"time":157200,"text":"The same thing that makes\nthem so interesting --"},{"time":159480,"text":"their small size --"},{"time":160800,"text":"also makes them impossible to work with."},{"time":163120,"text":"It's literally like trying to build\na statue out of a pile of dust."},{"time":166880,"text":"And we just don't have the tools\nthat are small enough to work with them."},{"time":170600,"text":"But even if we did,\nit wouldn't really matter,"},{"time":172920,"text":"because we couldn't one by one\nplace millions of particles together"},{"time":176840,"text":"to build a technology."},{"time":178760,"text":"So because of that,"},{"time":180000,"text":"all of the promise\nand all of the excitement"},{"time":182120,"text":"has remained just that:\npromise and excitement."},{"time":184920,"text":"We don't have any\ndisease-fighting nanobots,"},{"time":187320,"text":"there's no elevators to space,"},{"time":189400,"text":"and the thing that I'm most interested in,\nno new types of computing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193120,"text":"Now that last one,\nthat's a really important one."},{"time":195680,"text":"We just have come to expect"},{"time":197040,"text":"the pace of computing advancements\nto go on indefinitely."},{"time":200840,"text":"We've built entire economies on this idea."},{"time":203440,"text":"And this pace exists"},{"time":205200,"text":"because of our ability\nto pack more and more devices"},{"time":207680,"text":"onto a computer chip."},{"time":209400,"text":"And as those devices get smaller,"},{"time":211240,"text":"they get faster, they consume less power"},{"time":213520,"text":"and they get cheaper."},{"time":214960,"text":"And it's this convergence\nthat gives us this incredible pace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219560,"text":"As an example:"},{"time":220800,"text":"if I took the room-sized computer\nthat sent three men to the moon and back"},{"time":226240,"text":"and somehow compressed it --"},{"time":228400,"text":"compressed the world's\ngreatest computer of its day,"},{"time":231680,"text":"so it was the same size\nas your smartphone --"},{"time":234280,"text":"your actual smartphone,"},{"time":235560,"text":"that thing you spent 300 bucks on\nand just toss out every two years,"},{"time":238960,"text":"would blow this thing away."},{"time":241440,"text":"You would not be impressed."},{"time":242800,"text":"It couldn't do anything\nthat your smartphone does."},{"time":245320,"text":"It would be slow,"},{"time":246840,"text":"you couldn't put any of your stuff on it,"},{"time":249040,"text":"you could possibly\nget through the first two minutes"},{"time":251520,"text":"of a \"Walking Dead\" episode\nif you're lucky --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":253720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254760,"text":"The point is the progress --\nit's not gradual."},{"time":256959,"text":"The progress is relentless."},{"time":258680,"text":"It's exponential."},{"time":259959,"text":"It compounds on itself year after year,"},{"time":262320,"text":"to the point where\nif you compare a technology"},{"time":264520,"text":"from one generation to the next,"},{"time":266240,"text":"they're almost unrecognizable."},{"time":268240,"text":"And we owe it to ourselves\nto keep this progress going."},{"time":270880,"text":"We want to say the same thing\n10, 20, 30 years from now:"},{"time":274520,"text":"look what we've done\nover the last 30 years."},{"time":277200,"text":"Yet we know this progress\nmay not last forever."},{"time":279960,"text":"In fact, the party's kind of winding down."},{"time":282040,"text":"It's like \"last call for alcohol,\" right?"},{"time":284400,"text":"If you look under the covers,"},{"time":286080,"text":"by many metrics\nlike speed and performance,"},{"time":288680,"text":"the progress has already slowed to a halt."},{"time":291760,"text":"So if we want to keep this party going,"},{"time":293920,"text":"we have to do what we've\nalways been able to do,"},{"time":296200,"text":"and that is to innovate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297680,"text":"So our group's role\nand our group's mission"},{"time":300280,"text":"is to innovate\nby employing carbon nanotubes,"},{"time":302720,"text":"because we think that they can\nprovide a path to continue this pace."},{"time":306800,"text":"They are just like they sound."},{"time":308280,"text":"They're tiny, hollow tubes\nof carbon atoms,"},{"time":310760,"text":"and their nanoscale size,\nthat small size,"},{"time":313720,"text":"gives rise to these\njust outstanding electronic properties."},{"time":317400,"text":"And the science tells us\nif we could employ them in computing,"},{"time":321080,"text":"we could see up to a ten times\nimprovement in performance."},{"time":323840,"text":"It's like skipping through several\ntechnology generations in just one step."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328840,"text":"So there we have it."},{"time":330120,"text":"We have this really important problem"},{"time":332160,"text":"and we have what is basically\nthe ideal solution."},{"time":334560,"text":"The science is screaming at us,"},{"time":336240,"text":"\"This is what you should be doing\nto solve your problem.\""},{"time":341480,"text":"So, all right, let's get started,"},{"time":343120,"text":"let's do this."},{"time":344400,"text":"But you just run right back\ninto that double-edged sword."},{"time":347120,"text":"This \"ideal solution\" contains a material\nthat's impossible to work with."},{"time":350720,"text":"I'd have to arrange billions of them\njust to make one single computer chip."},{"time":355040,"text":"It's that same conundrum,\nit's like this undying problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359360,"text":"At this point, we said, \"Let's just stop."},{"time":361360,"text":"Let's not go down that same road."},{"time":363320,"text":"Let's just figure out what's missing."},{"time":365880,"text":"What are we not dealing with?"},{"time":367320,"text":"What are we not doing\nthat needs to be done?\""},{"time":369480,"text":"It's like in \"The Godfather,\" right?"},{"time":371280,"text":"When Fredo betrays his brother Michael,"},{"time":373600,"text":"we all know what needs to be done."},{"time":375280,"text":"Fredo's got to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377680,"text":"But Michael -- he puts it off."},{"time":379640,"text":"Fine, I get it."},{"time":380880,"text":"Their mother's still alive,\nit would make her upset."},{"time":383360,"text":"We just said,"},{"time":384800,"text":"\"What's the Fredo in our problem?\""},{"time":387120,"text":"What are we not dealing with?"},{"time":388560,"text":"What are we not doing,"},{"time":390120,"text":"but needs to be done\nto make this a success?\""},{"time":393200,"text":"And the answer is\nthat the statue has to build itself."},{"time":397280,"text":"We have to find a way, somehow,"},{"time":399240,"text":"to compel, to convince\nbillions of these particles"},{"time":403360,"text":"to assemble themselves\ninto the technology."},{"time":406360,"text":"We can't do it for them.\nThey have to do it for themselves."},{"time":409560,"text":"And it's the hard way,\nand this is not trivial,"},{"time":412720,"text":"but in this case, it's the only way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415600,"text":"Now, as it turns out,\nthis is not that alien of a problem."},{"time":419520,"text":"We just don't build anything this way."},{"time":421400,"text":"People don't build anything this way."},{"time":423440,"text":"But if you look around --\nand there's examples everywhere --"},{"time":426640,"text":"Mother Nature builds everything this way."},{"time":429560,"text":"Everything is built from the bottom up."},{"time":432240,"text":"You can go to the beach,"},{"time":433520,"text":"you'll find these simple organisms\nthat use proteins --"},{"time":436720,"text":"basically molecules --"},{"time":438000,"text":"to template what is essentially sand,"},{"time":440080,"text":"just plucking it from the sea"},{"time":441520,"text":"and building these extraordinary\narchitectures with extreme diversity."},{"time":444920,"text":"And nature's not crude like us,\njust hacking away."},{"time":447560,"text":"She's elegant and smart,"},{"time":449280,"text":"building with what's available,\nmolecule by molecule,"},{"time":452040,"text":"making structures with a complexity"},{"time":454200,"text":"and a diversity\nthat we can't even approach."},{"time":457320,"text":"And she's already at the nano."},{"time":459040,"text":"She's been there\nfor hundreds of millions of years."},{"time":461560,"text":"We're the ones that are late to the party."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464120,"text":"So we decided that we're going\nto use the same tool that nature uses,"},{"time":468320,"text":"and that's chemistry."},{"time":470000,"text":"Chemistry is the missing tool."},{"time":471480,"text":"And chemistry works in this case"},{"time":473560,"text":"because these nanoscale objects\nare about the same size as molecules,"},{"time":477400,"text":"so we can use them\nto steer these objects around,"},{"time":480040,"text":"much like a tool."},{"time":481760,"text":"That's exactly what we've done in our lab."},{"time":483840,"text":"We've developed chemistry\nthat goes into the pile of dust,"},{"time":487040,"text":"into the pile of nanoparticles,"},{"time":488560,"text":"and pulls out exactly the ones we need."},{"time":490960,"text":"Then we can use chemistry to arrange\nliterally billions of these particles"},{"time":494600,"text":"into the pattern\nwe need to build circuits."},{"time":497480,"text":"And because we can do that,"},{"time":498840,"text":"we can build circuits\nthat are many times faster"},{"time":501240,"text":"than what anyone's been able\nto make using nanomaterials before."},{"time":504480,"text":"Chemistry's the missing tool,"},{"time":505920,"text":"and every day our tool gets sharper\nand gets more precise."},{"time":509560,"text":"And eventually --"},{"time":510800,"text":"and we hope this is\nwithin a handful of years --"},{"time":513440,"text":"we can deliver on one\nof those original promises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516840,"text":"Now, computing is just one example."},{"time":518919,"text":"It's the one that I'm interested in,\nthat my group is really invested in,"},{"time":522480,"text":"but there are others\nin renewable energy, in medicine,"},{"time":526320,"text":"in structural materials,"},{"time":528080,"text":"where the science is going to tell you\nto move towards the nano."},{"time":531160,"text":"That's where the biggest benefit is."},{"time":533920,"text":"But if we're going to do that,"},{"time":535400,"text":"the scientists of today and tomorrow\nare going to need new tools --"},{"time":538600,"text":"tools just like the ones I described."},{"time":540760,"text":"And they will need chemistry.\nThat's the point."},{"time":544640,"text":"The beauty of science is that\nonce you develop these new tools,"},{"time":548320,"text":"they're out there."},{"time":549600,"text":"They're out there forever,"},{"time":550880,"text":"and anyone anywhere\ncan pick them up and use them,"},{"time":553760,"text":"and help to deliver\non the promise of nanotechnology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557320,"text":"Thank you so much for your time.\nI appreciate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560040,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}